The paper focuses on face detection and recognition using a convolutional neural network, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of end-to-end training and geometric transformation matrix also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of datasets and benchmarking indicates the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
